task.summary: Now running on new laptop, Windows 7, Scala 2.9, Google App Engine 1.6.4. Corrected test following WSJ page changes. All tests run and pass.
Got basic change working to work round empty story div issue. A test prove this works. Needs tidying.
Processed output from Instapaper which works around empty story div now creates its own story div, rather than leaving the body tag in.
Now it really does change a body tag into a story div when generating a workaround version from Instapaper.
Updated Tweeted Times URL, as the old one (twittertim.es) finally stopped working
Migrated to Google App Engine HRD datastore.

option.name: LAST_COMMIT_MESSAGE

MESSAGE.value: Added article (and remaining articles) count to document header.
Added easy link to mail an old document.
Updated Twitter Times network handler to cope with format change from them. Also updated ClnMe test to be a bit more robust.
Refactored TwitterTimesNetworkHandler.
Tidied an import statement.
Link to original now moved next to title.
Slicker matching code in Twitter Times network handler.
More elegant code in Twitter Times network handler, and more tests for it.
Made a bit of code a bit more Scala-ish
Simplified a bit of code.

Target added to ant build to compile tests and prep the application for upload. This is now used as the test target to avoid the mistake of seeing the tests pass and then thinking what's there is okay to upload.
Moved transaction methods into a trait to tidy up code.
Finally added login authentication on all pages. Fiddled with some boilerplate removal code with exception trapping and printing. Not great, but it works.
Deleted ClnMe code, as (a) it's not used in the application, and (b) the service seems to have disappeared.
Updated to deal with change in The Tweeted Times' changed format.
Less frequent article fetching to run up less costs in Google App Engine new pricing plan.
Corrected test following WSJ page changes. Added a couple of scripts which should start making this kind of thing easier.
